THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 209 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. The Director shall, with the approval of the Board, adopt
4 regulations to be instituted in each institution or facility which
5 govern the food served in institutions or facilities operated by the
6 Department. Such regulations must, without limitation:
7 (a) Require the Department and each institution or facility to
8 adopt the Good Food Purchasing Program or its successor
9 program;
10 (b) Prohibit the Department and any institution or facility
11 from entering into a contract or other agreement with a for-profit
12 food vendor; and
13 (c) Require a licensed dietitian or registered dietitian to
14 approve each meal or menu item provided to offenders in
15 accordance with the guidelines set forth in the most recent version
16 of the Dietary Guidelines for Americans published by the United
17 States Department of Agriculture and the United States
18 Department of Health and Human Services.
19 2. To the extent money is available for this purpose, the
20 Director shall establish and carry out a prison farm program to be
21 instituted in each institution or facility.
22 3. As used in this section:
23 (a) “Licensed dietitian” has the meaning ascribed to it in
24 NRS 640E.040.
25 (b) “Prison farm program” means an agricultural program for
26 the vocational training or employment of offenders in farming or
27 related activities.
28 (c) “Registered dietitian” has the meaning ascribed to it in
29 NRS 640E.080.
30 Sec. 2. The amendatory provisions of section 1 of this act do
31 not apply to a contract entered into before October 1, 2025, but do
32 apply to any renewal or extension of such a contract.
